# ChitNow — Codex PermissionRequest rule template
#
# These rules route matching shell commands into Codex's PermissionRequest
# flow, where ChitNow intercepts them and sends an approval request to your
# Apple Watch.
#
# INSTALL:
#   Merge into ~/.codex/rules/default.rules (create if it doesn't exist).
#   Then re-trust hooks in the Codex TUI: run /hooks and confirm.
#
# FORMAT: one pattern per line (plain prefix match or glob).
#   Lines starting with '#' are comments and are ignored.
#   Each non-comment line is matched as a prefix against the full command string.
#
# NOTE: ChitNow only receives commands that Codex routes here. Commands not
# matched by these rules are executed directly without Watch approval.

# Privilege escalation
sudo

# Destructive file operations
rm -rf
rm -r

# Force-push and history rewrite
git push --force
git push -f
git reset --hard
git clean -fd
git clean -f

# Remote script execution via pipe
curl
wget

# Overwrite system paths
> /etc/
> /usr/
